body:
We need a quiz about Bootstrap 4 so that students can auto-grade themselves in terms of their knowledge in bootstrap. 

This lesson will help you get inspired with questions:
http://docs.content.breatheco.de/lesson/learn-bootstrap-4/

At least 15 questions. Try to make students think and not just answer by memory.

### Here is how the JSON structure of a quiz looks like:

```json
{
    "info": {
        "slug":    "new",
        "name":    "Some fake name",
        "status":    "draft",
        "main":    "Some fake description",
        "results": "What do you want to say to whomever finishes the quiz?",
        "badges": [
            { "slug": "css_master", "points": 23 }
        ]
    },
    "questions": [
        {
            "q": "Sample Question",
            "a": [
                {"option": "some option",      "correct": true},
                {"option": "some other",     "correct": false}
            ]
        }
    ]
}
```

## More about the quiz JSON structure:

- This is an example of a quiz, the `slug` of the quiz is a unique identifier for it.
- Ignore the badges property, leave it as it is, it's experimental and we are not doing anything with that information right now.
- The name is the quiz main title shown to the students.
- Each question contains the answers object and the question itself:
```json
        {
            "q": "Sample Question",
            "a": [
                {"option": "some option",      "correct": true},
                {"option": "some other",     "correct": false}
            ]
        }
```
- You can have as many options as you want, but only one can be correct.

## How to Pull Request the quiz?

After finishing the quiz just push it to this folder between the other json files:
https://github.com/breatheco-de/assets/tree/master/apis/quiz/data
